        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:20PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 320 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 12 miles northeast of Mesita to 15
miles west of Los Lunas, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Western Albuquerque and Tohajiilee.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 125 and 147.
</description>
        <instruction>Blowing dust associated with strong thunderstorm winds can reduce
visibility below one quarter mile at times.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
